  <section id="about">
    <h2 class="section-title">About the Advocacy</h2>
    <p>Specialized nursing care procedures—such as catheterization, wound care, IV therapy, and tracheostomy care—require skill, precision, and updated knowledge. This advocacy champions continuous training, adherence to clinical standards, and patient-centered techniques to ensure every procedure is done safely and ethically.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="core-principles" id="principles">
    <h2 class="section-title">Core Principles</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Competency-Based Training:</strong> Encouraging simulations and certifications for skill mastery.</li>
      <li><strong>Patient Safety First:</strong> Advocating infection control, accurate documentation, and ethical handling.</li>
      <li><strong>Ongoing Education:</strong> Promoting CPD (Continuing Professional Development) among nurses.</li>
      <li><strong>Technology Integration:</strong> Leveraging tools and EHRs to support decision-making in specialized care.</li>
      <li><strong>Empathy in Action:</strong> Ensuring compassion in every procedure performed.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

